ZCZC RE73
GREENLAND VIA SAUDANES
230250 UTC DES 2018
SYNOPSIS /1800 UTC.:
A LOW 1003 HPA SOUTHWEST OF MEQQUITSOQ IS ALMOST STATIONARY AND ASSOCIATED
FRONTS GIVES WIDESPREAD SNOW AND SLEET TO THE SOUTHWESTERN WATERS.
A NEW LOW 984 HPA IS MOVING TOWARDS EAST TOWARDS LABRADOR AND CAUSING
A NEW FRONT WITH STRONG WIND SNOW AND SLEET TOWARDS THE SOUTHERN AND WESTERN
WATERS.
THE NORTHEASTERN WATERS HAVE A WEAK NORTHWESTLY FLOW AND EAST COAST HAVE
A FEW SNOW OR SLEET SHOWERS AND LOCALLY FOG
PATCHES.
